Key Lifetime Challenges
For connection-oriented 
protocols one choice is to use 
the same session key for the 
length of time that the 
connection is open, using a 
new session key for each new 
session.
A security manager 
must balance 
competing 
considerations:
For a connectionless protocol 
there is no explicit connection 
initiation or termination, thus 
it is not obvious how often 
one needs to change the 
session key.
The more frequently 
session keys are 
exchanged, the more 
secure they are.
The distribution of 
session keys delays the 
start of any exchange 
and places a burden on 
network capacity.
