Key Lifetime Challenges
Aprotocol calls for a hierarchy of keys:
Keys lower on the hierarchy used more
frequently, and changed more frequently to
thwart attacks.
A higher-level key, which is used infrequently
and therefore more resistant to cryptanalysis,
is used to encrypt a newly created lower-level
key so that it can be exchanged between
parties that share the higher-level key.
The term ephemeral key refers to a key that is
used only once or at most is very short-lived.
