X.509 Certificates
X.509
•X.509 defines a framework for the provision of
authentication services.
•Was initially issued in 1988 with the latest revision in
2000.
•Based on the use of public-key cryptography and digital
signatures.
•Does not dictate the use of a specific algorithm but
recommends RSA.
•Does not dictate a specific hash algorithm.
•Each certificate contains the public key of a user and is
signed with the private key of a trusted certification
authority.
